for your home with 'em.

114
00:05:17,840 --> 00:05:20,890
You'd have to be crazy not to
get a bushel of your very own.

115
00:05:21,850 --> 00:05:23,850
She's so creative.

116
00:05:23,890 --> 00:05:24,850
You, sir!

117
00:05:24,890 --> 00:05:26,600
Care to buy
some apples?

118
00:05:26,640 --> 00:05:27,600
Uh, no, thanks.

119
00:05:27,640 --> 00:05:28,730
Why not?

120
00:05:28,770 --> 00:05:31,060
I have plenty at home.

121
00:05:31,060 --> 00:05:32,150
Are you sure?

122
00:05:32,190 --> 00:05:34,360
Yes, I'm pretty sure.
You're pretty sure,

123
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:36,530
But you're not absolutely,
positively,

124
00:05:36,570 --> 00:05:38,610
completely, superduper sure,
are you?

125
00:05:38,660 --> 00:05:41,830
Uh, if I buy some apples,
will you please leave me alone?

126
00:05:41,870 --> 00:05:43,040
All right!

127
00:05:46,660 --> 00:05:48,330
You forgot your change!

128
00:05:48,330 --> 00:05:49,920
Whoo-Hoo!

129
00:05:49,960 --> 00:05:53,590
There's how you sell some apples
and get a cutie mark.

130
00:05:53,630 --> 00:05:55,840
So, what does my cutie mark
look like --

131
00:05:55,880 --> 00:05:57,630
A shopping bag
full of apples?

132
00:05:57,670 --> 00:05:59,760
A satisfied customer
eating an apple?

133
00:05:59,760 --> 00:06:00,800
Hmm.

134
00:06:00,840 --> 00:06:04,720
Maybe I got to increase
my sales figures first.

135
00:06:04,770 --> 00:06:06,890
You touch it,
you buy it!

136
00:06:06,930 --> 00:06:08,770
We take cash or credit.

137
00:06:08,770 --> 00:06:10,560
I'm sorry, ma'am.

138
00:06:10,600 --> 00:06:11,770
Ma'am!

139
00:06:13,610 --> 00:06:15,730
Now, Apple Bloom,
you can't just...

140
00:06:15,780 --> 00:06:18,030
That'll be four bits.

141
00:06:18,070 --> 00:06:19,950
I didn't put those
in my bag.

142
00:06:19,990 --> 00:06:21,370
Likely story.

143
00:06:21,410 --> 00:06:22,660
Four bits, lady.

144
00:06:22,700 --> 00:06:23,530
Apple Bloom!

145
00:06:23,620 --> 00:06:25,990
I am really, really sorry
about that.

146
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:27,120
She's new.

147
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:30,080
Here. Take these.
No charge.

148
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:32,000
And these.

149
00:06:34,960 --> 00:06:36,840
And these.

150
00:06:39,420 --> 00:06:41,840
Y'all come back now,
you hear?

151
00:06:44,010 --> 00:06:45,140
What?

152
00:06:45,180 --> 00:06:48,600
Sorry, little sis, but your
apple-selling days are over.

153
00:06:48,640 --> 00:06:49,520
What?!

154
00:06:49,560 --> 00:06:51,690
But how else am I gonna get
my cutie mark?

155
00:06:51,730 --> 00:06:54,110
Home. Now!

156
00:06:54,150 --> 00:06:55,610
Pbht!

157
00:06:55,650 --> 00:06:57,070
Hmph.

158
00:06:58,110 --> 00:06:59,190
Listen, sugar cube,

159
00:06:59,190 --> 00:07:01,860
I know it's hard to wait
for your very own cutie mark,

160
00:07:01,860 --> 00:07:04,030
but you just can't
force it.

161
00:07:04,070 --> 00:07:06,910
Besides, you're not
that grown up just yet.

162
00:07:06,950 --> 00:07:10,210
Ain't there other fillies
in your class without one?

163
00:07:10,210 --> 00:07:12,710
Well, twist
doesn't have hers yet.

164
00:07:12,710 --> 00:07:13,960
Do you think
you'd feel better

165
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:15,540
